-- CNP Assurances says in talks with Santander on European tie-up
-- By Leila Abboud
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 02:53AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, June 30 (Reuters) - French insurance group CNP Assurances <CNPP.PA> confirmed that it was in talks with Santander <SAN.MC> after a newspaper report said it was negotiating to buy 51 percent of the Spanish bank's Irish unit that sells insurance on consumer loans.

If the deal is finalised, CNP would pay about 350 million euros ($477.42 million) and Santander as would remain the minority shareholder, according to Les Echos newspaper.